main event: On June 24, 1963, a farmer observed round white objects in the sky near Versailles, Missouri.
interesting points: The observation lasted for about 20 minutes,The objects would dim and then light up again,Initial observation indicated the objects were at an altitude above 60,000 feet,The witness described the objects as about the size of a half-dollar held at arm's length,The sighting was observed through binoculars at dusk.
sighted object: round white objects in the sky
